ganga/python/GangaLHCb
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A few minor bug fixes, along w/ some updates to LHCbDataset:

* User can replicate an LFN directly using the LHCbDataFile, e.g. f =
LHCbDataFile('LFN:/.../file.dst'), then f.replicate('CERN-USER') or any "allowed" space token (do
f.replicate() for a list of allowed ones).

* An entire LHCbDataset can be replicated by simply calling dataset.replicate('CERN-USER')

* LHCbDataset's are now "scriptable", i.e. this works: 
  ds = LHCbDataset(files=['a','b','c'])
  ds[0] # same as ds.files[0]
  ds[-1] # same as ds.files[-1]
  ds[0:2] # same as ds.files[0:2], except returns a new LHCbDataset as opposed to a []

* An LHCbDataset can be "extended", e.g. 
  ds1 = LHCbDataset(files=['a','b','c'])
  ds2 = LHCbDataset(files=['d','e'])
  ds1.extend(ds2) # it's now ['a','b','c','d','e']
  ds1.extend(['f','g']) # and now ['a','b','c','d','e','f','g']


